data.content:
The root cause is that **Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi 10.0** upgraded to **OpenAPI.NET v2**, which has several breaking changes. Here's what changed and the fixes:

| .NET 9 (OpenAPI.NET v1) | .NET 10 (OpenAPI.NET v2) | Why |
|---|---|---|
| `Microsoft.OpenApi.Any.OpenApiString` | `System.Text.Json.Nodes.JsonValue` | `IOpenApiAny` types removed; `JsonNode` used instead |
| `OpenApiSecurityScheme` + `OpenApiReference` | `OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference` | Dedicated reference classes replace generic `OpenApiReference` + `ReferenceType` |
| `schema.Nullable = false` | `schema.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null` | OpenAPI 3.1 uses JSON Schema type arrays, not `nullable` keyword |

**Fixed code:**

```csharp
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;           // replaces Microsoft.OpenApi.Any
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models.References; // new: typed reference classes

options.AddOperationTransformer((operation, context, ct) =>
{
    var param = operation.Parameters.FirstOrDefault(p => p.Name == "api-version");
    if (param is not null)
    {
        // OpenApiString → JsonValue.Create
        param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
    }

    // OpenApiResponse unchanged
    operation.Responses.TryAdd("401", new OpenApiResponse { Description = "Unauthorized" });

    // OpenApiSecurityScheme + OpenApiReference → OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference
    var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2");
    operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
    {
        new() { [oAuthScheme] = scopes }
    };

    return Task.CompletedTask;
});

options.AddSchemaTransformer((schema, context, ct) =>
{
    if (schema.Properties is not null)
    {
        foreach (var property in schema.Properties)
        {
            if (schema.Required?.Contains(property.Key) != true)
                // Nullable property removed; clear the Null flag instead
                property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
        }
    }
    return Task.CompletedTask;
});
```

**Summary of the 3 breaking changes:**

1. **`OpenApiString` → `JsonValue.Create()`** — The entire `Microsoft.OpenApi.Any` namespace is gone. All `Example`, `Default`, and extension values are now `JsonNode`.

2. **`OpenApiSecurityScheme { Reference = ... }` → `OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2")`** — The generic `OpenApiReference`/`ReferenceType` pattern was replaced with strongly-typed reference classes under `Microsoft.OpenApi.Models.References`.

3. **`Nullable = false` → `Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null`** — OpenAPI 3.1 (which v2 targets) uses JSON Schema's type arrays (`"type": ["string", "null"]`) instead of the `nullable` keyword. `JsonSchemaType` is a `[Flags]` enum.
